We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant to:
reconcile the amount presented in the financial statements against the SLs of Accounts Payable, and make the necessary entry for the derecognition of Accounts Payable without SL;
prepare an adjusting entry for the recognition of unreleased checks by debiting Cash in Bank account and crediting Accounts Payable account amounting to ₱1,043,593.99, and update the SL pertaining to these unreleased checks;
prepare an adjusting entry to correct the recognition of the unutilized LDRRMF as Accounts Payable;
prepare an adjusting entry to record unrecognized expenses/assets and accounts payable incurred or received in 2022 that were settled in CY 2023 and restate the CY 2022 financial statements to reflect the effect of the prior period adjustment; and
submit supporting documents for the newly established Accounts Payable to support its recognition in CY 2023.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant to ensure that relevant information is supplied and available to the intended users of the financial statements, enabling them to make well-informed decisions based on a comprehensive understanding of the financial reports, henceforth:
prepare and submit the necessary supporting schedules/attachments on the notes to PPE;
reclassify loans payable as current and non-current liability and provide disclosures in the NFS;
revise the disclosure on the available balance of LDRRMF to include the correct amounts of 2019 and 2021 special trust funds, and continuing appropriations;
revise the presentation of original and final budgets, actual amount and balances of LDRRMF to coincide with the disclosure of LDRRMF in the NFS, after consideration of the above-mentioned inconsistencies;
reconcile the net cash flows from operating activities presented in NFS and the SCF; and
reconcile the actual amounts of SCBAA and SFPe. Reconciling items must be supported with computation schedules to support its validity.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
BAC Secretariat to post the NOA, NTP and the approved contracts in the PhilGEPS website within the prescribed period;
BAC to see to it that all posted performance securities are dated or its validity period covers what is required by law;
BAC to invite an observer coming from a duly recognized private group in a sector or discipline relevant to the procurement at hand to witness the procurement activities of the PE;
BAC Chairman to see to it that prior to contract signing of infrastructure projects, require the winning bidder to submit CSHP approved by the DOLE and other supporting documents;
BAC to strictly comply with the provisions of Section 17.3 and Annex C of the Revised IRR of RA 9184 in providing ample time to prospective bidders to examine the bid documents and prepare their respective bids, hence the municipality could avail of the best offer which is more advantageous to the government;
The BAC through its BAC Secretariat to prepare and send the Notification of Bid Submission and Notification of Bidding Result and ensure that the bidder receive the said documents;
BAC Secretariat to prepare minutes of the procurement activity conducted;
The BAC to ensure that all procurements made by the PE, under competitive bidding, strictly follow the proceedings and requirements of the bidding process;
The BAC and TWG to diligently carry out their responsibilities at every stage of the procurement process, ensuring that reports are meticulously prepared to accurately reflect actual dates and time of each activity;
For the project Rehabilitation of Ubbog Farm-to-Market Road, BAC, Municipal Accountant and Municipal Engineer to submit the documents not attached to the Disbursement Voucher and to correct those inconsistencies to reflect the actual winning bidder; and
Municipal Accountant to meticulously scrutinize all disbursement vouchers submitted for processing, ensuring that these are accurately and completely supported with the required documents before authorizing payments.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
GSO-designate to submit the Delivery Receipt of the items not yet supported by such document;
GSO-Designate to prepare AIR confirming the actual date of delivery of items;
Municipal Accountant to require the supplier to submit Delivery Receipt for all items delivered and consider the imposition of liquidated damages, if warranted; and
BAC and its TWG to properly consolidate items of similar specifications in the procurement process.

